-- PRESS DIGEST - Bulgaria - July 23
-- 
-- Wed Jul 23, 2014 02:45AM EDT
-- None



SOFIA, July 23 (Reuters) - These are some of the main stories in Bulgarian newspapers on Wednesday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

-- Sofia Court of Appeal left unchanged the restraining measures of the Corpbank's officials who were accused with large-scale embezzlement (Trud, Capital daily, 24 Chasa, Monitor). -- Bulgaria's government debt at the end of first quarter of 2014 increased by 1.4 percent from the fourth quarter of last year and by 2.3 percent from the first quarter of 2013, to 20.3 percent of the GDP, Eurostat data showed (Standart, Capital daily, Monitor). -- Tourist season in Bulgaria has not been affected by recent floods, Deputy Economy Minister Branimir Botev said (24 Chasa, Monitor). -- Police have closed off the area around the central bus station in Sofia and have evacuated all passengers due to unattended luggage for less than an hour . Several people were detained at a nearby police station (24 Chasa, Monitor).